## 📌 What I Learned Today

### 🔹 What is an End-to-End ML Workflow?

It is the **step-by-step pipeline** followed to build a machine learning solution

---

## 🔄 Complete ML Pipeline

### 1️⃣ Data Collection 📥

* Gather raw data from sources

---

### 2️⃣ Data Preprocessing 🧹

* Handle missing values
* Clean & format data
* Feature scaling

---

### 3️⃣ Feature Engineering 🔧

* Create & select important features

---

### 4️⃣ Model Selection 🤖

* Choose algorithm (Linear, Logistic, KNN, etc.)

---

### 5️⃣ Model Training 📚

* Train model on training data

---

### 6️⃣ Model Evaluation 📊

* Use metrics (Accuracy, MAE, etc.)

---

### 7️⃣ Model Improvement ⚙️

* Hyperparameter tuning
* Reduce overfitting

---

### 8️⃣ Prediction 🚀

* Use model on new data

---

## 🔥 Intuition (Very Important)

👉 ML is not just model building
👉 It’s a **full pipeline system**

💡 Missing any step = poor results

---

## 🧠 Key Takeaways

* ML follows a structured process
* Data preprocessing & features are critical
* Evaluation & tuning improve results

